Prior to drying, each CMR sample was uniformly loaded into the cylindrical stainless basket. So, it could be regarded as a cylinder with the diameter of 3.50 × 10–2 m and the length of 9.00 × 10–2 m. Effective moisture diffusivity (Deff) in this study can be calculated according to Fick’s second law. Therefore, the moisture movement in a cylindrical sample can be described by Eq. (9) [44].9MR=Mτ-MeM0-Me=4∑n=1∞1Bn2exp(-Bn2DeffτL2)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
