Previous studies showed that both drying temperature and air velocity influenced the drying process [54, 62]. Li et al. found that drying parameter K was a polynomial function of air velocity and a linear function of temperature, while drying parameter n was a polynomial function of air velocity and temperature [31]. Artnaseaw et al. determined the drying parameters k, a, n, and b of Midilli model as a function of drying temperature and drying pressure when Shiitake mushroom and Jinda chili were dried via vacuum heat pump [63]. Accordingly, the constants n and k were defined as the function of both drying temperature (T) and N2 velocity (U), respectively. According to the proposed regression equations in Table S7, Eq. (14) and Eq. (15) were developed to determine the drying parameters n and k of Weibull model.14n=a0+a1T+a2U+a3T2+a4U2+a5T3+a6U3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
